File Upload API and Authentication Types
1>Open CMD
2>Now install the JAR file
3>now type cd C:\Users\rkarekax\Downloads and press enter
4>now type java -jar file-upload-RestAPI.jar and press enter
5>Now it will run the API after that you can able to see the below things
5>now come to browser and in the URL section
6>type localhost:8080
7>It will show you to upload single and multiple API testing

The below one is the API Testing which we are using through Postman
URL to upload single file
POST : http://localhost:8080/uploadFile

URL to upload multiple files
POST : http://localhost:8080/uploadMultipleFiles

Now create the above 2 Request in the Postman

Single File Upload
1>Create new collection and give the name as File Upload
2>Click on new request and give the name as upload single file
3>select POST and past this URL : http://localhost:8080/uploadFile
4>Now click on Body
5>Select from-data 
6>Key will be file and type will be File
7>In the value browse the file and select the file
8>now click on send

Multi File Upload
1>Create new collection and give the name as File Upload
2>Click on new request and give the name as upload Multi files upload
3>select POST and past this URL : http://localhost:8080/uploadMultipleFiles
4>Now click on Body
5>Select from-data 
6>Key will be files and type will be File
7>In the value browse the file and select the multiple files
8>now click on send

Where these above files are getting uploaded.
It is getting uploaded in the below locations C:\uploads

Authentication Types
Basic authentication
For this we need user name and password, but it is not encrypted

Digest authentication
For this we need user name and password, but it is encrypted

Auth 2.0
For this we need to create PAT key, and it is highly encrypted authentication

You can also create a token from the github

For Normal Token
1>Login to GitHub
2>go to your profile and click on settings
3>click on developer settings
4>click on personal access token
5>click on generate new token (classic) for general use
6>Give the note name
7>select the expire date
8>select the scope by check mark
9>now go down and click on generate token

For OAuth Token
1>Login to GitHub
2>go to your profile and click on settings
3>click on developer settings
4>click on OAuth Apps
5>Click on new OAuth app
6>Give the application name
