Step 1: Request a user’s github identity
1>Go to Postman
2>select GET and Past this URL : http://github.com/login/oauth/authorize?client_id=e2e76f497363a381720d
3>select params
4>In key type client_id
5>in Value paste the client id token
6>now click on send
7>once you send open the above url in the browser to get the code
8>now the code which you will get the browser URL please copy that code

Step 2: Users are redirected back to your site by GitHub
1>Go to Postman
2>select POST and type this URL
3>select params
4>in key and value type these 3 things
•	client_id and value
•	client_secret and value
•	code and value
5>now click on send
6>now you will get the OAuth access token

Make sure while doing this activity the tomcat service should be running.

